rndm_def: Arugula, (Eruca sativa) is an edible annual plant, also known as rocket salad, rucola, rucoli, rugula, colewort, and roquette.
A black radish is a radish of the black radish plant
A whole raw mature broad bean.
A daikon radish is a radish of the daikon radish plant
A type of pea which is cultivated to produce dry peas.
A whole raw sprouted kidney bean.
A whole raw immature lima bean.
Mizuna (ミズナ（水菜）, "water greens"), is a cultivated crop plant from the species Brassica juncea var. japonica a dark green, serrated leafed plant
A leaf of a mizuna plant (Brassica rapa subsp. nipposinica).
Salad greens are leaf vegetables that are served raw in a salad.
A cabbage head from a Savoy cabbage plant.
A raw scallion is a scallion plant possibly with root removed and leaves trimmed
A whole raw mature winged bean.
